<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">Prayer for Lent 3</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Mar 09, 2015 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
 <b>A prayer for reconciliation.</b>
</p>

 <p>
God of love,
</p>

 <p>
We open our arms <br></br>
to hug and to hold, <br></br>
welcome and invite.
</p>

 <p>
With outstretched hands, <br></br>
we lower our defenses <br></br>
and accept the vulnerability <br></br>
that comes with love.
</p>

 <p>
Did the soldiers know <br></br>
what they were doing <br></br>
as they stretched the arms <br></br>
of Jesus onto the cross?
</p>

 <p>
Humiliated and scorned, <br></br>
the Eternal King <br></br>
chose vulnerability, love, <br></br>
and reconciliation <br></br>
instead of rejection.
</p>

 <p>
Give us the courage <br></br>
to do the same.
</p>

 <p>
 <i>Amen</i>
</p>


